OL,3,CWorld in Action interview brings back
OL,4,C'quiet terror' of late husband's HIV
OL,6,FOur Health Correspondent Helen Ford
OL,7,Fwrites:
OL,9,FJo-Anne Cohrs told me the report into
OL,10,Fthe contaminated blood scandal gave
OL,11,Fboth "relief and comfort" to those who
OL,12,Fhad faced what she describes as "cold
OL,13,Fshoulders, harsh judgements and a lack
OL,14,Fof sincerity" over many years.
OL,16,FAt last, she says, "the truth can no
OL,17,Flonger be buried or shredded".
